Metlib is a collection of python libraries for Atmospheric Science.

As for Chinese Users, please notice the differece between the pronunciation of Metlib and Matlab. 

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Requirements:
Python 2.4+
dateutil
numpy and scipy: www.scipy.org
matplotlib and mpl_toolkits.basemap: http://matplotlib.sourceforge.net/
pyproj: pyproj.googlecode.com
netcdf4-python: http://code.google.com/p/netcdf4-python/

metlib.misc.download : requires requests .
metlib.misc.multiprocess : requires python2.7 (multiprocessing) .

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tips:

To import most common utils, you may use:
>>> from metlib.kits import *

large or messy modules: 
	metlib.data, metlib.io, metlib.misc, metlib.plot, metlib.phy 
have "_all.py" for importing.
e.g.,
>>> from metlib.misc._all import *
or import submodules individually:
>>> from metlib.misc.misc import get_sys_argv

other modules may be imported directly:
>>> from metlib.color import *

